# Adapter Layer Architecture

**Before writing any code here, read all of the following:**

- `docs/architecture/integrations.md` — port–adapter design principles P1–P6
- `docs/architecture/authentication.md` — Okta M2M token handling
- `docs/architecture/quality-and-delivery.md` — fake-before-merge requirement
- `docs/adr/ADR-004-domain-contracts-pydantic.md` — domain contracts and error types

## Spec-first workflow

Check for an existing spec in `docs/specs/adapters/<adapter-slug>-spec.md` before writing
anything. Specs are authored by humans by default. Only draft a spec from
`docs/specs/templates/adapter-spec-template.md` if the human explicitly asks you to, and
wait for approval before saving it or writing any code.

## Non-negotiable constraints

**Satisfy the port structurally — no subclassing (P4)**
An adapter must match its port's method signatures so the type checker accepts it. Do not
inherit from the Port Protocol. The composition root is the only place that imports and
instantiates a concrete adapter — agent and tool modules never import from `src/adapters/`.

```python
# src/adapters/ai_gateway/llm.py
class AiGatewayLlmAdapter:           # no explicit (LlmPort) base class
    def invoke(self, request: LlmRequest) -> LlmResponse:
        ...
```

**Vendor SDKs and raw DTOs stay inside the adapter (P2, P3)**
Vendor SDK types, raw API payloads, and serialization logic must not leak past the adapter
boundary. Translate raw responses to domain models before returning. Translate inbound domain
models to vendor formats internally.

**Convert vendor errors to domain errors — no retries (P6)**
Catch all vendor/SDK exceptions and re-raise as typed domain errors from `src/domain/`.
Never add retry loops, backoff, or fallback logic inside an adapter — failure policy belongs
in the workflow orchestration layer.

```python
try:
    raw = self._client.complete(prompt=request.prompt)
except VendorSdkError as exc:
    raise LlmError(message=str(exc)) from exc   # domain error only
return LlmResponse(text=raw.text)
```

**Fake required before merge (P5)**
Every new adapter must have a corresponding fake in `tests/fakes/` in the same PR.
The fake implements the same Port Protocol as the real adapter and is used in all unit
tests and default CI — no real external calls without `@pytest.mark.external`.
